# NET-NEW under lead-uiwu (CRITICAL clone-path regression). FACET 2 (workspace ownership).
# EMPIRICAL FINDING (product authority, 2026-06-28, reproduced launching shopsystem-
# templates against bc-base/launcher v0.3.33): with --repo-url supplied, the in-container
# clone fails "/workspace/.git: Permission denied" because /workspace is created
# root:root while the agent + clone run as user vscode (uid 1000). The working 5-day-old
# messaging container has /workspace owned vscode:vscode — so this re-pins the contract
# that regressed. Single behavior: a launched BC's /workspace is writable by the agent
# user because it is OWNED by that user, so the clone performed as that user succeeds.
#
# COEXISTENCE the architect must enumerate at dispatch:
#   - scenario 02 (@scenario_hash:62e1e005e9ece9f3) — pins the clone lands in the
#     workspace but ASSUMES the write succeeds; 67 pins the OWNERSHIP precondition that
#     makes that write succeed (no Permission denied). Complementary, no conflict.
#   - scenario 44 family (@scenario_hash:6952248a419ca56b / f838de07a80749f9 /
#     d6296d959f851be5) — no host-filesystem credential mounts; orthogonal (ownership of
#     /workspace is not a credential mount). Coexists unchanged.
#
# Pin observable container state only (ADR-018; no BC source read) — ownership is
# observable via stat inside the running container, and the clone outcome via its exit /
# error string. @bc: and the reproducing @scenario_hash on dispatch are the Architect's;
# the block-only @scenario_hash below is the PO's authoring hash.
  @scenario_hash:4154b0ea63d0516b
  Scenario: a launched BC's /workspace is owned by the agent user so the in-container clone performed as that user succeeds without Permission denied
    Given the shopsystem-bc-launcher BC is installed
    And bc-container launch is run with BC name "shopsystem-templates" with a valid repo URL
    And the container "bc-shopsystem-templates" is running
    When the ownership of the "/workspace" directory inside the running container is inspected
    Then "/workspace" is owned by the agent user "vscode" (uid 1000), not by root
    And the clone performed into "/workspace" as the agent user completes without a "/workspace/.git: Permission denied" error
